Here is a Matlab script that exports the complete file names and paths of a specified directory into a new text file:

```matlab
% Specify the directory path
dir_path = '/path/to/directory/';

% Get the file information of the directory
dir_info = dir(dir_path);

% Create a new text file for storing the file names and paths
fileID = fopen('file_list.txt','w');

% Loop through each file in the directory
for i = 1:numel(dir_info)
    % Check if the current file is a directory
    if ~dir_info(i).isdir
        % Get the full file path
        file_path = fullfile(dir_info(i).folder, dir_info(i).name);

        % Open the file for reading
        file = fopen(file_path,'r');

        % Get the file size
        file_size = dir_info(i).bytes;

        % Read the file contents
        file_contents = fread(file,file_size,'*char')';

        % Write the file name and path to the text file
        fprintf(fileID,'%s\n',file_path);

        % Close the file
        fclose(file);
    end
end

% Close the text file
fclose(fileID);
```

To use this script, replace `/path/to/directory/` with the path to the directory you want to export the file names and paths of. The script will create a new text file called `file_list.txt` in the same directory as the script. The text file will contain the complete file names and paths of each file in the specified directory, one per line, in the same format as the original file. The file size of the exported file will be equivalent to the original file.

