  ssl: {
    ca: fs.readFileSync(process.env.COCKROACHDB_CA_CERT),
    cert: fs.readFileSync(process.env.COCKROACHDB_CLIENT_CERT),
    key: fs.readFileSync(process.env.COCKROACHDB_CLIENT_KEY),
    rejectUnauthorized: true,
  },
});

await client.connect();
```

8. Deploy your Next.js application to Vercel. Each deployment will use a separate CockroachDB database.

With these steps, you should be able to successfully deploy a project using both Next.js and CockroachDB on Vercel while allowing for preview deployments and creating a separate database for each deployment.

